%20before%20the%20Congress%20leadership%20declined%20the%20invitation%20for%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20consecration%20ceremony%2C%20Karnataka%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20DK%20Shivakumar%20defended%20the%20decision%20of%20his%20government%20to%20celebrate%20the%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20by%20saying%20%E2%80%9Cultimately%20we%20all%20are%20Hindus%E2%80%9D.%20In%20saying%20so%2C%20he%20ignored%20the%20numerous%20Hindus%20and%20non-Hindus%20who%20would%20view%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20secular%20state%20celebrating%20a%20religious%20ritual%2C%20as%20objectionable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20predictable%20response%20to%20this%20objection%20is%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cseparation%20of%20church%20and%20state%E2%80%9D%20arrangement%20does%20not%20work%20in%20a%20country%20like%20India%20where%20the%20state%20actively%20engages%20with%20religious%20institutions%2C%20ignoring%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20is%20not%20an%20outlier%20in%20its%20interaction%20with%20religion.%20In%20Germany%2C%20the%20state%20funds%20religious%20schools%20and%20facilitates%20the%20collection%20of%20taxation%20imposed%20by%20churches%20on%20their%20congregants.%20In%20Australia%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20it%20is%20constitutionally%20permissible%20to%20extend%20the%20level%20of%20aid%20available%20for%20private%20secular%20schools%2C%20to%20religious%20schools%20as%20well.%20Cooperation%20between%20state%20and%20religion%20is%20commonplace%20in%20the%20field%20of%20education%2C%20because%20funding%20private%20schools%2C%20many%20of%20them%20run%20by%20religious%20organisations%2C%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20teaching%20secular%20subjects%20may%20be%20more%20efficient%20than%20the%20construction%20of%20additional%20public%20schools%20by%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrance%20is%20often%20touted%20as%20the%20strictest%20form%20of%20separation%20of%20church%20and%20state%20due%20to%20their%20philosophy%20of%20La%C3%AFcit%C3%A9%20as%20embodied%20in%20their%201905%20Act.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%201905%20Act%20permitted%20France%20to%20take%20ownership%20of%20existing%20religious%20sites%20and%20ensure%20their%20maintenance%2C%20provided%20the%20state%20did%20not%20construct%20new%20religious%20sites.%20The%20Debre%20law%20of%201959%20allows%20public%20funding%20of%20religious%20schools%20in%20France%20for%20the%20teaching%20of%20secular%20subjects.%20These%20nuances%20are%20forgotten%20due%20to%20the%20way%20La%C3%AFcit%C3%A9%20has%20been%20imposed%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20to%20prohibit%20religious%20outfits%20in%20certain%20settings%2C%20disparately%20impacting%20Muslims.%20In%20many%20democracies%2C%20the%20notion%20of%20a%20strict%20separation%20of%20state%20and%20religion%20is%20a%20myth.%20Between%20a%20strict%20separationist%20state%20and%20a%20theocracy%2C%20there%20are%20various%20forms%20of%20institutional%20arrangements%20between%20state%20and%20religion%2C%20based%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20neutrality%20and%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EState%20neutrality%20towards%20religion%20is%20celebrated%20as%20a%20virtue%20in%20democratic%20societies%2C%20but%20neutrality%20on%20its%20own%20is%20not%20a%20self-defining%20concept.%20One%20aspect%20of%20neutrality%20is%20that%20the%20state%20should%20not%20encourage%20or%20discourage%20individuals%20to%20follow%20a%20particular%20religion.%20However%2C%20state%20practices%20are%20not%20limited%20to%20incentivising%20religious%20conduct%2C%20they%20can%20also%20send%20out%20a%20message%20that%20a%20particular%20religious%20identity%20has%20a%20higher%20status%20compared%20to%20others.%20This%20principle%20of%20neutrality%20was%20articulated%20by%20Justice%20Sandra%20O%E2%80%99Connor%2C%20the%20first%20woman%20judge%20of%20the%20U.S%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20to%20argue%20that%20when%20the%20state%20endorses%20a%20religious%20identity%2C%20it%20%E2%80%9Csends%20a%20message%20to%20non-adherents%20that%20they%20are%20outsiders%2C%20not%20full%20members%20of%20the%20political%20community%2C%20and%20an%20accompanying%20message%20to%20adherents%20that%20they%20are%20insiders%2C%20favored%20members%20of%20the%20political%20community.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20democratic%20society%2C%20one%20religious%20identity%20should%20not%20be%20treated%20as%20superior%20to%20others%20by%20the%20state.%20This%20is%20why%20even%20though%20Germany%20does%20not%20follow%20a%20strict%20separationist%20model%2C%20the%20Constitutional%20Court%20ordered%20the%20removal%20of%20crosses%20from%20courtrooms%20in%201973%2C%20and%20crucifixes%20from%20public%20schools%20in%201995.%20In%202010%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Japan%20ruled%20against%20the%20use%20of%20public%20land%20for%20a%20Shinto%20Shrine.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Canada%20in%202015%20put%20an%20end%20to%20the%20use%20of%20Christian%20prayers%20by%20the%20Mayor%20of%20Saguenay%20to%20open%20official%20sessions%20of%20the%20Municipal%20Council%2C%20reasoning%20that%20the%20state%20should%20neither%20favour%20nor%20hinder%20any%20particular%20belief.%20This%20is%20the%20same%20value%20that%20forms%20the%20basis%20of%20Article%2027%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20which%20prohibits%20the%20use%20of%20taxpayer%E2%80%99s%20money%20for%20the%20promotion%20or%20maintenance%20of%20any%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20state%20should%20not%20endorse%20or%20disapprove%20any%20particular%20religious%20identity%20especially%20since%20it%20does%20not%20have%20an%20official%20religion.%20The%20United%20Kingdom%20is%20cited%20by%20some%20as%20a%20model%20of%20democracy%20with%20an%20official%20religion%2C%20the%20Anglican%20Church.%20However%2C%20nearly%20half%20the%20UK%20population%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20follow%20any%20religion%2C%20and%20only%2012%25%20are%20affiliated%20with%20the%20Anglican%20Church.%20Religion%20is%20not%20a%20major%20factor%20in%20the%20political%20discourse%20in%20the%20U.K.%20In%20contrast%2C%20religion%20heavily%20informs%20Indian%20political%20discourse%2C%20and%2097%25%20of%20the%20population%20are%20religious.%20Despite%20the%20de-jure%20position%20of%20the%20Anglican%20Church%2C%20courts%20in%20England%20have%20reasoned%20that%20the%20precepts%20of%20a%20particular%20religion%20cannot%20have%20a%20higher%20position%20in%20law%20in%20comparison%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11121926%2FScreenshot-2024-01-11-at-12.18.29-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11121926%2FScreenshot-2024-01-11-at-12.18.29-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11121926%2FScreenshot-2024-01-11-at-12.18.29-PM-300x128.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11121926%2FScreenshot-2024-01-11-at-12.18.29-PM-1024x437.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692418%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Ram%20Temple%20under%20construction.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40ShriRamTeerth%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20state%20uses%20its%20instrumentalities%20to%20promote%20religious%20activities%2C%20it%20enters%20the%20forbidden%20sphere%20of%20religious%20endorsement.%20The%20endorsement%20of%20religious%20identities%20to%20reap%20political%20dividends%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20governments%20run%20by%20the%20BJP.%20The%20Punjab%20Assembly%20passed%20a%20law%20to%20make%20the%20telecasting%20of%20Gurbani%20from%20the%20Golden%20Temple%20free%20of%20cost.%20The%20previous%20Congress%20government%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20organized%20the%20National%20Ramayana%20Festival%20and%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20ordered%20temples%20in%20the%20state%20to%20conduct%20special%20pujas%20on%20the%20day%20of%20the%20inauguration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir.%20However%2C%20very%20few%20acts%20of%20endorsement%20can%20match%20the%20scale%20at%20which%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20BJP-run%20state%20governments%20are%20promoting%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20inauguration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UP%20government%20allocated%20Rs%20100%20crore%20for%20a%20series%20of%20religious%20activities%20in%20temples%20across%20the%20state%20and%20the%20UP%20Minister%20Dharmveer%20Prajapati%20announced%20that%20there%20would%20be%20live-streaming%20of%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20in%20all%20jails%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20U.P%20Government%20also%20allotted%20money%20to%20make%20a%20music%20album%20on%20the%20life%20of%20Lord%20Ram%2C%20and%20the%20Mayor%20of%20Indore%20ordered%20malls%20to%20install%20replicas%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir.%20Doordarshan%20will%20also%20feature%20a%204K%20live%20broadcast%20of%20the%20temple%20consecration%20ceremony%2C%20with%2040%20cameras%20installed%20at%20various%20locations%20around%20the%20temple.%20The%20UP%20government%20is%20also%20undertaking%20187%20beautification%20projects%20in%20Ayodhya%20with%20a%20budget%20of%20Rs%2030%2C570%20crore.%20The%20chief%20minister%20has%20made%20no%20secret%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20projects%20in%20Ayodhya%20are%20linked%20to%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir.%20BJP%20states%20have%20decided%20to%20impose%20religious%20norms%20on%20all%20their%20constituents%20by%20declaring%2022nd%20January%20as%20a%20dry%20day.%20All%20educational%20institutions%20in%20UP%20will%20also%20be%20closed%20due%20to%20the%20ceremony.%20In%20the%20latest%20development%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20declared%20that%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%2022nd%20also%20as%20a%20holiday%20for%20central%20institutions%20and%20offices.%20These%20are%20clear-cut%20examples%20of%20state%20endorsement%20of%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20strength%20lies%20in%20the%20idea%20that%20no%20single%20religious%2C%20linguistic%2C%20ethnic%20or%20social%20identity%20forms%20the%20basis%20of%20our%20nation.%20In%20order%20to%20protect%20this%20strength%2C%20we%20must%20remain%20vigilant%20against%20the%20problematic%20fusion%20of%20religion%20and%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EArvind%20Kurian%20Abraham%20is%20an%20advocate%20with%20an%20LLM%20from%20Harvard%20Law%20School%20and%20a%20B.A%20LL.B%20(Honours)%20from%20NUJS.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705669214000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11120348%2FPrime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_performing_Bhoomi_Pujan_at_%25E2%2580%2598Shree_Ram_Janmabhoomi_Mandir%25E2%2580%2599_in_Ayodhya_Uttar_Pradesh_on_August_05_2020.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fshould-the-state-celebrate-the-ram-mandir-ceremony%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20strength%20lies%20in%20the%20idea%20that%20no%20single%20religious%2C%20linguistic%2C%20ethnic%20or%20social%20identity%20forms%20the%20basis%20of%20our%20nation%2C%20which%20requires%20vigilance%20on%20our%20part%20to%20avoid%20the%20problematic%20fusion%20of%20religion%20and%20the%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fshould-the-state-celebrate-the-ram-mandir-ceremony%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Teacher%20accused%20of%20poisoning%20husband's%20smoothie%20with%20toxic%20plant%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705668900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-sarah-scheffer-poisoned-husband_6426308.jpg%3F20240119090151%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fteacher-accused-of-poisoning-husbands-smoothie-with-toxic-lily-of-the-valley-plant-in-us-13051587%22%2C%22